<title>UK: BP says share buyback will be before next AGM.</title>
<headline>BP says share buyback will be before next AGM.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>British Petroleum Co Plc said on Tuesday its plannned buy-back of $500 million of shares would be before the next annual shareholders' meeting.</p>
<p>Chief executive John Browne also told reporters BP was on track for a toal contribution from so-called self-help -- volume growth and reduced costs of more than $500 million for 1997 as a whole.</p>
</text>
